Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.58,0:00:04.44,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Next up is Taylor. \NAnd beyond him is Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.44,0:00:06.62,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna duke it out with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.62,0:00:10.94,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna take on that driving genius who's \Nnothing like anyone I've ever seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.29,0:00:13.95,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The lead group has left Route 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.95,0:00:18.17,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,and are turning right \Nonto the Ashinoko Skyline.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.86,0:00:23.11,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,There's a large gap, \Nthen here comes the third-place group.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.73,0:00:24.96,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.96,0:00:27.24,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I can't deny I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.72,0:00:29.98,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 86 is right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.31,0:00:33.00,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't fallen back as much as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.64,0:00:35.68,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,It's a quirk of the wet conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.19,0:00:38.52,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,You can have a 600hp-plus monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.52,0:00:43.43,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,but without the traction to translate that \Npower onto the road, it's essentially wasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.93,0:00:48.16,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,In large groups like this one, \Ndrivers jockey for position
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.16,0:00:52.00,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,in a way that also hampers\N their own overall race pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.94,0:00:57.17,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,This might turn into a lengthy \Nexplanation. Should I continue?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.17,0:00:58.74,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Please go ahead, Ikeda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.21,0:01:04.21,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,This is the conclusion I have drawn\N after a long career in racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.21,0:01:07.69,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,When you drive on a circuit \Nwith an off-the-shelf model,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.69,0:01:13.09,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say 400hp is about the max your \Naverage person can adequately control.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.43,0:01:18.90,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,But on public roads, \Nthat figure is quite a bit lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.90,0:01:21.06,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Drive systems make a difference...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.06,0:01:24.85,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,...but I'd estimate it to be\N between 300 and 350hp.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.85,0:01:27.21,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It's really that much lower?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.53,0:01:32.77,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,But the cars near the top of MFG\N tend to exceed 600hp.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.77,0:01:34.03,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.03,0:01:37.49,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,But I think when it comes to MFG...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.49,0:01:41.19,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,that much power isn't actually necessary.
