Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.65,0:03:50.87,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like people may have the wrong idea\N about that one regulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.87,0:03:55.35,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,There are a few misleading traps\Nin the grip-to-weight regulation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.35,0:03:58.05,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,that have made major \Ndifferences in performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.52,0:04:05.01,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I get the feeling going into detail\Nwould upset Ryo Takahashi, so I won't,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.01,0:04:09.52,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,but a lot of premium-brand imports have \Nmore power than can actually be tapped into,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.52,0:04:12.52,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,bottled up by beefy tires\N and electronic systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.52,0:04:16.15,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,and get sold to the more affluent\N as status symbols.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.61,0:04:19.54,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,It seems absolutely ridiculous to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.29,0:04:21.75,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,But getting back on-topic...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.28,0:04:24.81,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,In wet conditions like what we have today,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.81,0:04:29.41,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,the amount of horsepower available to the \Ndriver on public roads lowers even further.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.64,0:04:32.54,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Down to between 200 and 250hp max.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.54,0:04:36.37,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,At the risk of being misunderstood, \Nthat's around where I'd put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.37,0:04:38.50,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,That's a huge decrease.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.50,0:04:42.09,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,But that number comes as quite a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:49.72,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The max output of a 2-liter NA \Nlike the Toyota 86 GT is exactly 200hp.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.97,0:04:51.27,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.51,0:04:57.73,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,This rain has all but erased the handicap \Nin power the 86 has to the rest of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:05:06.28,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I think the fans should keep that in mind \Nas they watch the race unfold from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.65,0:05:11.46,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,A heaven-sent wind in the form of this rain\Nappears to be lifting Katagiri Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.24,0:05:13.20,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.55,0:05:16.66,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the third-place group\Ncrossing the start-finish line.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:22.80,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? There seems to be two distinct lines \Nthrough the left and right gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.80,0:05:25.01,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,That's not something you see too often.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:29.01,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say that due to \Nhow narrow the gates are,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:32.56,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,the drivers were a bit anxious \Nabout going through at top speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.81,0:05:35.52,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,The spray was obscuring \Ntheir vision badly enough
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:39.73,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,for them to want to leave as much of \Na gap as possible to the cars in front.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.58,0:05:43.39,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:48.51,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,We might be looking at another \Nrare instance of rain-induced behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.74,0:05:52.40,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,More cars fly through the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.40,0:05:55.86,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The race is one-third done\Nas we enter the second lap!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.21,0:06:25.11,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The Godly Fifteen's monster machines\N are battling the rain itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.11,0:06:27.93,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Will only the most \Ntechnically-gifted drivers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.93,0:06:30.45,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,be able to assert themselves\N from here on out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.15,0:06:36.51,Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Up ahead, Lake Ashinoko's death zone \Nbares its fangs, waiting for fresh prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.96,0:06:59.73,Italics,Koki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ready to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.12,0:07:04.57,Italics,Koki,0000,0000,0000,,The riskiest stretch of the race\N that all the drivers hate...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.05,0:07:06.07,Italics,Koki,0000,0000,0000,,the death zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.04,0:07:08.50,Italics,Koki,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make my move there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.84,0:07:30.26,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The leading cars are entering \Nthe death zone for the second time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.58,0:07:58.16,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Sawatari in the 4 is breathing down \Nthe 12's neck like he's chasing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.77,0:08:03.75,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,This is touch and go! You can practically \Nfeel the tension with these risky maneuvers!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:05.71,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I daren't look away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.18,0:09:49.45,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And the 4 takes the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.45,0:09:53.27,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Beckenbauer has been toppled!
