Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.49,0:10:04.88,Top,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,MF Ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.07,0:10:11.92,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,At long last, Beckenbauer has been toppled!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.92,0:10:15.59,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,We've just seen a remarkable\N change for the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:18.55,Default,Office Worker A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed they didn't crash\N in all that rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.55,0:10:23.25,Default,Audience C,0000,0000,0000,,You see luxury cars worth tens of \Nmillions of yen get scrapped all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.25,0:10:25.52,Default,Audience C,0000,0000,0000,,after a single slip-up in MFG.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.76,0:10:27.98,Default,Office Worker B,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Godly Fifteen for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.98,0:10:30.17,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,They made contact three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:32.65,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Ikeda-san, can you \Nbreak down that overtake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.01,0:10:36.11,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm shocked he even tried \Nthat move in the death zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.42,0:10:39.39,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as if Beckenbauer made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.39,0:10:43.08,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Sawatari-kun just fired it into the turn\N way beyond the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.30,0:10:45.72,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,The contact itself was accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.72,0:10:50.50,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,The 12 was aiming for the apex \Nof the corner like every driver does,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.50,0:10:54.34,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,and didn't anticipate that \Nthe 4 would stick his nose in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.74,0:10:59.97,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,The nudge to the unloaded rear corner\N unbalanced the 12 and sent it wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:03.68,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,And the time it took to correct\N the slide made all the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.48,0:11:07.22,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,The two other times they made contact...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:11.52,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Well, how else can I put it? \NIt was like a clash of emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.94,0:11:16.40,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,After clashing over their lines, \Nthe 4 emerged with the advantage...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.40,0:11:21.50,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,...letting him floor it \Neven as he brushed the guard rail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.05,0:11:25.32,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,It was an incredible display\N by both drivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.64,0:11:31.66,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,That might have been the most \Ndramatic overtake in MFG history!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.35,0:11:41.85,Italics,Beckenbauer,0000,0000,0000,,I give you credit for forcing me \Nto get serious, even if just for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.38,0:11:45.26,Italics,Beckenbauer,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll pay you back double\N for that humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.26,0:11:49.23,Italics,Beckenbauer,0000,0000,0000,,First place is a bad fit \Nfor that cheap French vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.23,0:11:53.93,Italics,Beckenbauer,0000,0000,0000,,It belongs exclusively to me \Nand my mighty Porsche!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.65,0:12:02.86,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.40,0:12:05.82,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,Michael actually got overtaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.45,0:12:09.61,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that's a first \Nsince he started in MFG.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.12,0:12:13.31,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,If he finishes second, \Nit'll be a real shock to the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.52,0:12:20.94,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,He'll probably hole up in his bedroom for \Ntwo or three days without eating anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.31,0:12:26.70,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,That boy's absolutely helpless without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.59,0:12:32.34,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,He's arrogant, self-centered, moody, \Nand he can't express himself very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.02,0:12:35.76,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt he'll ever get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.63,0:12:40.47,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,But when it comes to racing, he never loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.47,0:12:43.11,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's the only thing he's good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.29,0:12:49.45,Italics,Agnes,0000,0000,0000,,Michael losing in a contest \Nlike that is inconceivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.79,0:13:18.77,Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(466,342)}The group vying for third \Napproaches the Mikuni Pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.09,0:13:23.74,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The six-strong group threads its way\N through the death zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.44,0:14:32.30,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.74,0:14:40.19,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,I can't accelerate if you're there, damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.15,0:14:44.61,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's a race, \Nbut that's too aggressive, dumbass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.84,0:14:47.07,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,You won't make the turn like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.91,0:14:51.57,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.94,0:14:53.04,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Drifting?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.82,0:15:08.18,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! It's the Mikuni Pass, \Nand the 86 has the 5 in its sights!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.18,0:15:11.59,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,There's just no keeping\N Katagiri Kanata quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.59,0:15:16.39,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He's making his move \Nfrom the back of the group!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.69,0:15:21.31,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Ikeda-san, what's your take on \Nthe overtake the 86 just made?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.27,0:15:28.32,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I can't accurately break down \Nthe maneuver Katagiri-kun just pulled.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.98,0:15:35.28,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,For someone like Car 5's Sakamoto Yudai \Nto get swept aside as easily as that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.72,0:15:38.12,Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,One thing I can tell you\Nis the Mikuni Pass
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:44.69,Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,is a long stretch that climbs uphill \Nbefore a sudden switch to going downhill.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.69,0:15:47.63,Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,While racing drivers \Nare good with lateral Gs,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.63,0:15:50.26,Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,they don't often have \Nto deal with vertical ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.92,0:15:57.47,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,In situations like that, no matter how brief,\N people tend to lose their sense of balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.87,0:16:03.82,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I think that created the slight opening \Nin Sakamoto-kun's approach to the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.19,0:16:07.88,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,And Katagiri-kun didn't let \Nthe opportunity go begging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.88,0:16:11.98,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,I'd almost say he was expecting it,\N and aimed to get it done there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.30,0:16:23.12,Italics,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,My brother drilled that kind of trick \Ninto me back during our Project D days.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.59,0:16:26.50,Italics,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,For street racers, it's Overtaking 101.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.98,0:16:32.47,Italics,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,This just shows it's been passed down \Nfrom Fujiwara Takumi to Katagiri Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.27,0:16:34.93,Italics,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,But I've got a trick of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.60,0:16:38.60,Italics,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,One I'm waiting to unleash.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.99,0:16:49.03,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,That thing Kanata just did\Nis called drifting, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.03,0:16:53.46,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen him do it before, but it always\N looks like he's starting to slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.04,0:16:58.41,Italics,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I don't have to move \Nthe lower places around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:01.62,Italics,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,The Angel Cam always \Nzooms in right on my butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:02.56,Default,Uehara,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.56,0:17:03.71,Default,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.71,0:17:06.37,Top Italics,Uehara,0000,0000,0000,,And now, a question for Moe-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.66,0:17:09.14,Default,Uehara,0000,0000,0000,,If you could go anywhere, \Nwhere would you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.14,0:17:13.09,Default,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,Hm... I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.96,0:17:18.80,Default,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know! In Asagaya in Tokyo, \Nthere's this famous BBQ place
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.80,0:17:22.28,Default,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,that's supposed to be {\i1}impossible{\i0} \Nto get reservations for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.28,0:17:26.23,Default,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to go there, \Neven it's just the one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:34.03,Default,Uehara,0000,0000,0000,,BBQ? I was expecting you to give the fans\N a more romantic answer, Moe-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:40.98,Default,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, my fans all know I love a bit of meat, \Nso I doubt they'll be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.98,0:17:45.19,Default,Uehara,0000,0000,0000,,I think General Manager Joyu's \Na regular at that restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.19,0:17:46.71,Default,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.71,0:17:49.07,Top Italics,Uehara,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you should ask him to take you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.07,0:17:52.25,Top Italics,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,Please, General Manager?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:56.38,Top Italics,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,Take me to the BBQ place!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.79,0:17:58.79,Default,Staff A,0000,0000,0000,,That's obviously not happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.79,0:18:03.35,Default,Staff B,0000,0000,0000,,The general manager's a busy man. \NHe doesn't have the spare time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.86,0:18:09.05,Top Italics,Moe,0000,0000,0000,,Can we, General Manager?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.47,0:18:13.13,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. After they've nailed the \Nchoreography for their new song,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:16.24,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take them all out as a reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:20.16,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The battle in the death zone continues!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.62,0:18:23.08,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Sawatari Koki!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:24.49,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Beckenbauer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.49,0:18:27.26,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And Katagiri Kanata!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.71,0:18:30.67,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The trio of young lions that \Nhave caught Ikeda-san's eye
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.67,0:18:34.05,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,surge through the rain \Nin Ashinoko's death zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.03,0:18:45.10,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.39,0:18:48.56,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,Sakamoto's Audi was behind me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.12,0:18:51.44,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd this red car come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.23,0:18:54.27,Default,Osihi SC,0000,0000,0000,,Booth to Daigo! Do you read me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.66,0:18:56.90,Italics,Osihi SC,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your wits about you \Naround the 86 behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.12,0:18:59.65,Italics,Osihi SC,0000,0000,0000,,It's fast going into the corners.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.65,0:19:03.62,Italics,Osihi SC,0000,0000,0000,,That's how he slipped past the 5. \NIf you're not careful, you'll be next!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.62,0:19:05.23,Italics,Osihi SC,0000,0000,0000,,So be careful! Over!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.29,0:19:10.75,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,"Be careful" my ass.\NDon't you have any {\i0}useful{\i1} advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.75,0:19:13.50,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,This death zone is so slippery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.50,0:19:18.92,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm already pushing as hard as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.81,0:19:33.65,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,The stability control just won't let up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:36.13,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,My fronts and rears\Nare slipping and sliding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.08,0:19:52.04,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hell. My front's getting away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.96,0:20:01.34,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,The downhill slope is too sleep.\NGotta stop it from going into a half-spin!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.76,0:20:07.99,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And the 3 spins out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.89,0:20:14.31,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It's now facing the wrong way\N as it slides off the road!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.19,0:20:18.36,Italics,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm screwed. Game over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.17,0:20:31.47,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it doesn't look good. \NI don't think he'll be rejoining the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.47,0:20:34.28,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Oishi Daigo is out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.69,0:20:37.09,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I just hope he's not hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.63,0:20:40.59,Top Italics,Central Audio,0000,0000,0000,,Control Center to the driver\N of Car 3. Do you read?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.47,0:20:45.05,Top Italics,Central Audio,0000,0000,0000,,Please respond! \NIf you're hurt, please let us know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:51.08,Top Italics,Central Audio,0000,0000,0000,,Driver of Car 3, do you hear me?\N Driver of Car 3!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.45,0:20:54.65,Default,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,Oishi here. I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.47,0:20:57.48,Default,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't really hit anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.85,0:21:00.32,Default,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and get me out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.73,0:21:03.03,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Oishi's unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.03,0:21:04.79,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.79,0:21:06.49,Default,Crowd,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.83,0:21:10.93,Top Italics,Crowd,0000,0000,0000,,Center to Rescue 3, \Nplease retrieve the driver for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.93,0:21:15.08,Top Italics,Crowd,0000,0000,0000,,We'll send out a tow truck for\Nthe car once the race is done. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.48,0:21:24.59,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Guess Oishi blew it in his Lambo. \NI'm just glad he's not hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.38,0:21:28.55,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I've gained\N a position by default.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.59,0:23:37.43,Italics,Narrator,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Turn 17: A Cruel Reality.